# RuboCop

- Run RuboCop only on the lines you actually changed:
  ```bash
  bundle exec rubocop path/to/file.rb:10-25
  ```
  This avoids fixing unrelated warnings in untouched code.
- Fix violations before committing. Husky/lint-staged will not block the commit, but CI will.
- Do not edit `.rubocop.yml` to silence a violation in the file you are working on; either fix the code or, if the rule is genuinely wrong for the project, raise it separately.
